Sec. 66-197. - Required community meeting before public hearing.
Before a public hearing may be held on a petition for a conditional zoning district, the petitioner must file in the
office of the town clerk a written report of at least two community meetings held by the petitioner. The community
meetings shall be held prior to the planning board's consideration of the petition. Notice of such a meeting shall be
given to property owners and tenants adjacent to the proposed project and within 500 feet of the area to be
